Decapsulation
ğŸ”¼ Receiver Side (Decapsulation)

The reverse happens at the destination:
Physical â†’ Data Link â†’ Network â†’ Transport â†’ Application
Each layer removes its header and passes the rest up.
Example:

Ethernet removes Ethernet header
IP removes IP header
TCP/UDP removes its header
Application gets the raw data
Just like opening nested envelopes: [Frame] â†’ [Ethernet] â†’ [IP] â†’ [TCP/UDP] â†’ [Data]


1. Find Host mac
Pickup any packet and select 'Ethernet', you'll see Src and Dst mac address.

2. Find host IP address
Select 'Internet Protocol' frame and you'll see Source Address and Destination Address.

3. Hostname - Find DNS, DHCP, NetBios or HTTP protocol.
Filter packet with DHCP
Select DHCP protocol -> Option (12) Host Name
OR
Filter with dns
Expand 'Domain Name System (query)" ->  Expand "Updates" -> Expand second option -> Look for "Domain Name"


